social_posts.post_text: These photos are fueling my self-esteem

No treat this Halloween for me, instead I tricked myself into being productive and studying instead. This Halloween I dressed up as a responsible student 🤪. 

Also is green my color?
I’ve seen how the Texas A&M cult works now.
My brother said I don’t look like wet noodle anymore.
Todays been a day, full of frizzy hair and lack of sleep.

It’s official… I’m a snack

Also finally found women’s jeans with pockets 😝

December 3rd- International Day of Persons with Disabilities. 

Most people will never know I have a chronic illness, kidney disease, and skin issues unless I told them. Disabilities, Illnesses, and Diseases are not always visible, and that lack of visibility can mean a lack of understanding and empathy from others. 

I’ve gone through the good, the bad, and the ugly to get to where I am. It lights up my world knowing that more resources/information/aid are being created by the minute to support people with disabilities.

social_posts.post_text: Reposting this since I had forgotten to add my favorite photo the first time
Photo dump. My favorites are at the end.
Had to break out my Christmas Dress
The four nations lived in harmony and peace… the last photo makes this make sense.
And here I was thinking I was going to trip, fall, and die walking along the Las Vegas strip in these heels.

Biggest takeaways from this year:

1. Acknowledge the negatives in your life but do not let them control you. 
2. Your ambitions should not be limited by your conditions.
3. Life made me a high maintenance girl. 😂
4. Seeing is not always believing.
5. You are your first advocate.
